snippet.textDisplay:
The Croatian Parliament voted unanimously on March 1, 2019, to adopt the Council of Europe Convention against Trafficking in Human Organs, becoming the eighth European nation to ratify the treaty.

The Convention was drafted in 2015 after the European Parliament passed a resolution in 2013 condemning the Chinese regime’s “state-sanctioned organ harvesting from non-consenting prisoners of conscience in China, including from large numbers of Falun Gong practitioners imprisoned for their religious beliefs, as well as from Uyghur and Tibetan prisoners.”

snippet.textDisplay: I use notepad all the time in coding or moving information from one program to another, especially when copy/pasting from a microsoft program.  There isnt always the option to right click paste as plain text where I work as they actually disable the right click option for security reasons or some bullocks.  So I end up needing to copy from say Outlook, paste into notepad to strip it of all the hidden MS text/fontmencoding nonsense, then copy from that into where I need the information.  I simply cannot function without notepad.  There is really no easier way to strip hidden text encoding when going from microsoft to another program.
